My bedroom

I go there every day
And I find myself always happy or sad.
It is cozy and very small
but it gives me a feeling
of peace and comfort.

My bed, then my guitar, 
my desk,
where  I spent long hours writing.

My corner, my altar, my palace,
the field of all battles,
a leading man to be hunted
and ballroom for a party

Ilusión

Madre, qué loca idea tengo!
Quisiera ser poeta y no una nina
per no de los malos, sino buena.
No creo que es tan fácil!

Me imagino mi nombre
sobre una pasta blanca,
las librerías llenas
de gente comprando.
Mi familia encantada,
mi corazón alegre,
y mi mente creando
más y más pensamientos.

Dream

Mother, that crazy idea I have. I would like to be a poet and not a child and not bad but good. I do not think it's so easy.

I guess my name on a white paste, bookstores full of people buying. My delighted family, my cheerful heart, and my mind creating more and more thoughts.

A Dream

A good night with a very clean sky. Birds singing melodies without rhythm.

The wind feels when a lament says, an old white beard when he says "I love you".

A quiet girl thinks and composes a dream, the leaves of the trees say a thought.

She is silent and reason, he wants to catch a dream, a dream that escapes because she does not own it.

And her mother calls her, wants to give some advice: "Look girl, it's late, you composed your dream."

Is that mother ... You do not understand? Life escapes me! That life is just a happy thought.

A Dream: One night very tall with a very clear sky,  the birds that sing melodies without rhythm. The wind that was felt when he said a sad tale, an old man with a white beard when he said "I love you." A girl quieted thinking and composing a dream, the leaves of the trees said a thought. She quiets and reasons, wants to trap a dream, a dream that escapes her because she doesn't want damage. A her mother calls her, wants to give her a piece of advice: "Look, honey, it is very late, I have made you a dream." It's that mother... You don't understand? Oh, how life escapes me! That life that is only a happy thought.

sin volver hacia atrás.

I am not nothing
I feel the sun
I feel that living
is the best

I see a flower bloom
I feel when the sun burns
This is to truly live!

I want to share this message with the children
Because I am like them
When they feel the rain fall
It will be to live

Amor

te quiero mas y mas.

Cuando mi corazon palpita
te dedico una sonrisa,
una sonrisa que exprese todo lo que no podria
explicar con palabras.

No se si tu lo sabes,
pero te amo en secreto.
Mi amor es mas grande que el mar,
y mis sentimientos mas claros
y sinceros
que una ola al reventar.

El cantar de la Iluvia

Creo que suéno y pienso que la montana
más alta carera, que las nubes mas altas cogere.
Sera cierto lo que dice la Iluvia en su cantar,
lo que dijo la otra noche cuando la luna
me contaba su pesar?

Yo soy nueva, contese.
No te entiendo ni comprendo tu cantar.

Quieres oir lo que yo pienso?
Solamente es un sueno.

I tell my pains to the air
So that it can notice my suffering

When the hours pass
and my cries have stopped
I feel that my living has ended

That I am like a rose
that I was marching
that i do not have color
nor do I interest anyone

Sufro

Cuando me siento sola
digo al aire mis penas
para que se dé cuenta que sufro.

Cuando pasan las horas
y mi llanto ha cesado
siento que mi vivir ha terminado,

que soy como una rosa
que ya está marchitando,
que no tengo color
ni le intereso a nadié.

The lord watched us from heaven sharing with us the greatness, the greatness of living and being united.

Laughing, wanting, we have been praying, asking the lord in heaven.

About the little leaves she said, "These are butterflies." Pedrito laughed with his sister. Juanita, showing him the yellow flowers, said, "These are pretty little birds." The grateful wasp
One time, a wasp caught herself in a spider web. A mouse that was passing the place, upon seeing the scared wasp in the web, sympathized with her and helped her. He broke the web with his sharp teeth and the wasp could escape. "Thank you!" she said to her friend the mouse. "I will never forget this good action." Then, he flew. A short time after, while the mouse was gnawing on delicious cheese, a fox was waiting to catch him. In that moment, the wasp arrived flying and upon realizing the danger to his friend, he quickly stung the fox. Before the pain, the greedy fox disappeared immediately.

"Thanks!", said the fly to its friend the mouse. Never will I forget this good action. Later, the fly returned. A little time later, while the mouse gnawed a delicious block of cheese a cat waited to trap it. In that moment, the fly arrived and upon realizing his friend's danger began to rapidly peck the ear of the cat. Before causing harm to the mouse, the cat disappeared immediately.

un abuelo y una abuela tenian una gllinita a la

El huevo era dorado.

El abuelo lo golpeo
y el huevo no se partio.

La abuela lo golpeo
y lo mismo ocurrio.

El gato y el perro jugaba y la mesa se cayó

Pronto, su pena acabó, porque "Pinta" cacareó.
Puso otro huevo, blanquito pero ya no dorado.

y la tortuguita

que vivian en el mar,
se encontraron
con una tortuguita
y se burlaron de ella,
porque, según ellos,
tenia un cuerpo muy feo.

En ese momento,
pasó una fuerte corriente
que estrelló a los peces
contra las rocas.
- Escóndete! - le gritaron
a la tortuguita

One day a sly fox invited to dinner at his neighbor stork. To tease her, put on the table a flat dish with liquid food.

STORK, despite his efforts, he could not eat with its long beak. Instead, the fox with his tongue, quickly gobbled all the food.

Lugo, with mocking voice, the fox asked the stork.

- It has been satisfied dear neighbor?
-- Very much! - Answered the coriander.
- Tomorrow, I will offer a sign succulent. I beg you to accept my invitation.

When they page through the story books, the small children identify the words related to the figures they see. Little by little, carried by their curiosity, they associate, relate, interpret, understand, and describe the images, expressing the contents with their own words. At this age, the stories can serve in two ways: to train them and to develop in them the basic abilities of listening and of talking before beginning formal lessons and literature. 

For this reason, the stories that integrate this book are brief and simple and are carefully selected and adapted for children that are beginning to learn how to read. The attractive and interesting illustrations that appear in its pages serve to stimulate their oral expression. 

With this educational material, we propose to contribute to our children an education as good parents and in all moments, give thanks for nature and ask appreciation for the marvelous work of God. Let's look, at the same time, to give them situations in which they are helped to think about the fundamental virtues of their life, and above all, that they are pushed to put them to practical use. 

That, starting when they are young:
Learn to cultivate friendship and be united.
Honor the truth and be honest and lawful. 
Be accustomed to do the right things.
Appreciate the force and the work of the people around them. 
Respect each other and respect everyone else. 
Care for the children and have a special care and consideration for the sick and the old.
Don't resort to violence.
Take care of and honor Nature.
Cultivate and honor Peace.

-The authors.

Young children when flicking through storybooks identify words by connecting them with the figures observed. Gradually, they are driven by their curiosity, associate, relate, interpret, understand and describe images, expressing the contents with their own words. At this age, then, stories can serve a dual function: to entertain and go developing in them the basic skills of listening and speaking before starting the formal learning of reading and writing.
For this reason, the stories that make up this book are short and simple and are carefully selected and adapted for children beginning to learn to read. The attractive and interesting illustrations in its pages are intended to stimulate oral expression.
With this educational material, we intend to help our children to be educated as good Peruvians and that, at all times, love nature and can appreciate the wonderful open from God. We seek also to create situations that will help them think about fundamental values ​​for their life and, above all, to encourage them to implement them.

"Oh!" said the butterfly. The hollow is very small, but we will give you a small site. The rain continued to fall. Suddenly, a jumping bird arrived and said, "My feathers are wet and I cannot fly."
